ìóŸRarchive/external_nushell_repo_backup/nushell.github.io/blog/2023-07-07-twin0202.mdŸ@5e32826727ac2606de85407d659a2bf83b78ee51b5fa67e2ae8955bcb404ec48πThis week in Nushell #202ëßNushell⁄‰jntrnr 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/9589] changed how 
``let``
 works with pipelines
, 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/9600] moved to using a safer shell integration default setting
, and 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/9587] disallowed blocks as first-class values
, and 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/9585] use an easier-to-read date format in prompt
, and 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/9578] fix a few clippy issues
1Kinoti 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/9614] improved subtyping
, and 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/9613] allowed tables to have annotations
Yethal made lots of test-runner improvements: 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/9622] test-runner: Performance improvements + regex match for test include/exclude
, and 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/9611] test-runner: Add option to exclude single test and module
, and 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/9406] Implement annotations support in test runner
WindSoilder updated 
``watch``
 to 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/9606] use notify-debouncer-full(based on notify v6) instead of notify v4
, and 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/9547] Bracketed paste refactor
NotLebedev created 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/9453] a command to get individual keys
sholderbach 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/9618] updated 
``proc-macro2``
 lock to fix the nightly build
, and 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/9612] excluded deprecated commands from completions
, and 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/9609] documented 
``fn pipeline()``
 used with 
``nu!``
 tests
, and 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/9605] removed unnecessary parentheses
hanjunghyuk 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/9623] fixed 
``explore``
 crashes on 
``{}``
YassineHaouzane 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/9616] fixed update engine_state when history.isolation is true (#9268)
nibon7 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/9610] replaced 
``users``
 with 
``nix``
 crate
amtoine 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/9608] simplified the 
``nu!``
 tests for 
``last``
 and 
``first``
 commands
, and 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/9404] REFACTOR: move the 0% commands to 
``nu-cmd-extra``
Hofer-Julian 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/9607] added a 
``pwd``
 command to stdlib
IanManske 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/9603] fixed the 
``headers``
 command handling of missing values
rusty-jules created 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/9594] Fix: return all headers with the same name from 
``http <method>``
baehyunsol 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/9582] made the behaviours of 
``last``
 and 
``first``
 more consistent
fdncred 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/9581] fixed the right prompt in the default_env.nu
, and 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/9579] fix typo in deprecated message: 
``$nu``
 should be 
``$env``
bgmort 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/9576] added a useful example to 
``http options``
 documentation
